news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet approves amendment in township policy
news.para: Under the policy made for UP Housing and Development Board and development authorities to encourage private investment in housing schemes, the developer had to pay urban development fees at the time of clearance of a detailed project report (DPR).

news.title: Hong Kong property agencies suing Evergrande to recover commissions
news.para: Centaline filed a suit against Evergrande in September to recover HK$3.1 million ($398,196) in overdue commissions, a court filing showed.

news.title: Sobha's sales bookings up 49% at Rs 1,030 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Sobha informed that sales bookings in volume terms rose to 13,48,864 square feet in Q2 of this fiscal from 8,91,700 square feet in the same quarter of last financial year.

news.title: New HUD rule aimed at preventing public housing evictions in U.S.
news.para: Under a new rule from the Department of Housing and Urban Development, tenants in HUD-subsidized public housing cannot be evicted for nonpayment without providing them 30 days' notice and information about available federal emergency rental assistance.

news.title: Evergrande's debt storm batters more Chinese builders' bonds
news.para: Both Fantasia and Kaisa Group saw their dollar-denominated bonds slump as much as 11 cents on Tuesday after Fantasia's bonds had been pummelled to below 20 cents on the dollar on Monday following its missed payment.

news.title: SC directs probe into collusion of Tihar jail officials with ex-Unitech promoters
news.para: It also directed suspension of Tihar Jail officials, pending proceedings against whom cases will be lodged as per the report, following ED's disclosure that the Chandra brothers were conducting business from prison.

news.title: Businesses must make disclosures more reader-friendly: Nutan Gaba, CFO, Home First
news.para: Lack of appropriate business-relevant disclosures create a disparity of information for public shareholders as against the nominee shareholders on the board, Nutan Gaba says.

news.title: AHFCs' loan book grows 10% to Rs 60,468 crore in June: Report
news.para: The 30+ days past due (dpd) for some select affordable housing finance companies (AHFCs) increased to 7.2 per cent as of June 30, 2021, from an estimated 3.2 per cent as of March 31, 2021, though headline 90+ dpd remained under control, it said.

news.title: Hong Kong needs to tackle housing shortage, says Carrie Lam
news.para: At the centre of plans announced by Lam in her last policy address in this term of office is a Northern Metropolis on the border with the mainland's technology hub of Shenzhen, covering 300 square kilometres.

news.title: Spain's government eyes rent controls in new housing bill
news.para: Government ministers approved draft rent control legislation during a weekly Cabinet meeting on Tuesday. Vulnerable families and young adults in Spain's biggest cities would be the main beneficiaries of the proposed law, the government said.

news.title: Mumbai: Metro 2A to offer 17,500 sq ft on rent on Andheri West station
news.para: The Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA) is constructing Line 2A (D N Nagar to Dahisar) via the Link Road. This route’s station at DN Nagar is named as Andheri West.

news.title: Gurugram: Pipes laid in new sectors, but few builders apply for water connection
news.para: Seeing the lukewarm response, the department of town and country planning (DTCP) has now decided to issue notices to the remaining developers asking them to apply for the water connection within 15-20 days.

news.title: Now, exclusive residential enclave for Goa police officers
news.para: This scheme, implemented through the Goa Police Welfare Society, will entail no financial implication to the department, but will enable officers to own their dream house.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC asks citizens to suggest way out on PAP units issue
news.para: The BMC has now decided to construct only 4,000 PAP units in Chandivali by ‘cashless’ means which will cost it around Rs 2,498 crore.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA recovers Rs 150 crore in four years
news.para: UP-RERA has decided about 30,500 complaints out of 38,500 complaints filed with it in the last four years. There are 2,959 projects registered with UP-RERA out of which 1,125 projects, i.e. about 38 per cent of the projects have been completed.
